review_data: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2021
name: Amazon Customer
title: The best apricots I've had in years
review: So, so scrumptiously wonderful!They are good for all applications.I love them just plain, but they're delicious stewed with equal parts of muscat wine or ginger beer and water with a little sugar,a couple cinnamon sticks and a couple star anise.A few of those with a dollop of Greek yogurt and you have yourself a worthy summer dessert so flavorful it will blow your mind.Chop and add them to sweet bread doughs, like pannetone, with golden raisins, dried cranberries and pine nuts -- and does it ever make the best French toast!Truly, I cannot tell you how fantastic these apricots are!

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2021
name: Amazon Customer
title: GROSS CHEMICAL SMELL AND TASTE!ü§Æü§Æü§Æ
review: These dried apricots smelled overwhelming of some kind of plastic like chemical! I tried to eat them and literally gagged! I was used to ordering "Sincerely Nuts" dried apricots...and thought I would try some other kinds. BIG MISTAKE! I only like California apricots not the Turkish kind which I find tasteless and too sweet. I like the sharpness of the higher vitamin C content of California dried apricots. Some of the apricots in a handful from this box didn't even taste vaguely like apricots, others tasted only of chemicals! I DO NOT RECOMMEND THESE AT ALL!!
